    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paintings on animal hide, usually American bison or elk. Prime examples represent the traditional Plains Indian artistic practice of painting on either tanned or raw animal hides.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
